  "title": "DRIVER",
  "description": "<p><strong>Key Duties and Responsibilities:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>Driving & Delivery:</strong> Transporting items (parcels, goods, or people) from warehouses to clients, retail outlets, or residential locations.</li><li><strong>Vehicle Maintenance:</strong> Conducting daily inspections (tires, lights, fuel, brakes) and keeping the vehicle clean.</li><li><strong>Logistics & Route Planning:</strong> Planning routes for maximum efficiency and meeting strict delivery deadlines.</li><li><strong>Loading/Unloading:</strong> Manually loading and unloading goods, which often requires physical strength and stamina.</li><li><strong>Documentation & Communication:</strong> Obtaining proof of delivery, processing invoices, updating tracking systems, and reporting any incidents or delays to dispatch. </li></ul><p><strong>Requirements and Skills:</strong></p><ul><li><strong>License:</strong> A valid driver’s license, often with a clean driving record (e.g., Class 3 in Singapore, C1 in UK for larger vans).</li><li><strong>Physical Fitness:</strong> Ability to lift, bend, and move heavy items throughout the day.</li><li><strong>Skills:</strong> Good customer service, communication skills, and navigation skills.</li><li><strong>Independence:</strong> Ability to work alone and manage time effectively. </li></ul>",
